ignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":5,"created_at":"2021-09-09T00:22:06Z","updated_at":"2021-09-09T08:29:18Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"In tags, all dashes should be replaced by underscores.\r\n\r\nThe reason is that in a vanilla call to `set_tags`, one would write `set_tags(tag_name=tag_value)`, but this will break if `tag_name` has a symbol in it that is not permitted in a python variable name (for instance, a dash).\r\n\r\nFor each tag, the changes need to be done:\r\n* in `registry/_tags` \r\n* all estimators where it is set\r\n* any other logic that accesses the tag, including: concrete estimator inits (dynamic tags), base class plumbing, and the tests.\r\n\r\nvscode \"find in files\" allows to highlight all occurrences.\r\n\r\nIf someone would like to work on this, please make yourself known here and pick one tag first, to keep changes small and avoid duplication.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1397/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1397/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}